36	Action for the Oceans  Youth leaders raising awareness for the Oceans, together!	2021-11-06 00:00:00+00	2021-11-06 00:00:00+00	Join us for this special hybrid event with a virtual platform to showcase inspiring actions for the oceans from youth leaders around the world!  Peace Boats Ocean and Climate Youth Ambassadors from Small Island Developing States and Youth for the SDGs scholars will be presenting their work from various countries including Fiji, Seychelles, Trinidad and Tobago, India, Mauritius, Chile, Mexico and more. Through a storytelling training program in partnership with the creative changency, Pendulum, this years ocean youth leaders will share their experiences to highlight the 2021 UN World Oceans Day theme of The Ocean: Life and Livelihoods.Through education and outreach, Action for the Oceans aims to strengthen creative skills and innovative solutions to achieve the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals, with a focus on SDG 14 for Life Below Water.Works will be shared via our digital platform and a reception will be held at the Selina Hotel in Chelsea, New York on the evening of June 11, Friday.	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/events_036.png	global	\N	2021-04-28 06:24:51.038858+00	2021-04-28 06:24:51.038858+00	\N	\N	\N	\N	APPROVED	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	f	en	\N	\N	\N	gpml
37	COVE Demo Day  Virtual	2021-10-06 00:00:00+00	2021-10-06 00:00:00+00	COVE  Where the best ideas in ocean technology come to life!Located in what was once the Canadian Coast Guard facility on Halifax Harbour, COVE is home to local and global ocean technology businesses, post-secondary institutions, and marine-based and service businesses that support the ocean sector. The COVE site features extensive marine facilities with two large, deep-water piers, office space, an incubator and space for shops and labs.COVE is a community that brings together the best and the brightest to push ocean tech advances to market. Its a space that fosters innovation and cross-pollinates expertise, ideas, and resources among members, COVE is where business growth, opportunity, and technical advances happen.On June 8 and June 10, 2021, attendees of the H2O Conference will have the opportunity to watch the latest in ocean technology highlighted on the Halifax Harbour. One registration to the H2O Conference also gets you access to COVE Demo Day broadcasts, too!	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/events_037.png	global	\N	2021-04-28 06:24:51.045299+00	2021-04-28 06:24:51.045299+00	\N	\N	\N	\N	APPROVED	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	f	en	\N	\N	\N	gpml
