36	Plastic Bank: Stopping ocean plastic while improving the lives of collector communities	2013	124	Established Company	In market	t	\N	national	[]	Description: How it Works\nIn Plastic Bank recycling ecosystems, collectors collect ocean-bound plastic (plastic collected within 30 miles of the ocean or waterway leading to an ocean) and deposit their recyclables at a local Plastic Bank branch or certified partner location. The plastic is sorted by type and colour, then weighed. The corresponding value is deposited into their digital account. Plastic Bank members receive a bonus in addition to the market value for their plastic. This ensures Plastic Bank members receive a stable and fair earned income. They can store and redeem the value at any time at a Plastic Bank branch or certified partner location.\n\nWhen a collector registers with Plastic Bank they receive a blockchain-secured digital wallet, virtual identity information, trust score and credit score. Through the digital platform, collectors and their families can become eligible for health insurance and school tuition. Our co-op community model empowers co-op members to gain co-op voting rights, equal profit sharing and shared ownership of their local programs.\n\nA branchs ongoing participation with Plastic Bank requires that they comply with Plastic Banks code of conduct for transparent ethical sourcing and maintain the required trust scores and standing.\n\nTypes of Plastic Collected\n- Mixed Plastic\n- HDPE\n- PET\n- PP\n- PS\n- LDPE\n- PVC\n- ABS\n- Caps\n- Custom Plastics\n\nBuilt for Trust\nPlastic Banks platform is designed for unlimited scale while maintaining speed, transparency and security through the use of IBMs enterprise-level technology stack. The technology stack utilizes blockchain and HyperLedger Fabric on private LinuxOne servers and the IBM Cloud.\n\nUtilizing the power of blockchain, Plastic Bank has created a tokenized reward system. Plastic Bank digital tokens act as loyalty points or credits, earned by recycling, with a guaranteed liquidation value of 0.01 USD per token. This system securely provides savings, cashless spending, and instant value distribution, with guaranteed delivery of the value promised to the members.\n\nPlastic Bank digital rewards can only be created by Plastic Bank. Digital rewards are not available through a public exchange. The creation of a token is matched with funds in a bank account controlled by Plastic Bank. Bonus rewards are instantly unlocked to eligible members at the time of exchange per kilogram of eligible material. In most programs, branches receive a distribution/reporting bonus upon verified re-sale of the equivalent amount of materials they rewarded to their collectors. Creating end-to-end trust and audibility.\n\nImpact Metrics\nSince the starting operations in Haiti in 2016, Plastic Bank has achieved the following impact:\n- 13,396,103 kg of plastic prevented from entering the ocean - thats the equivalent of 669,805,150 plastic bottles\n- 20,692 total collectors engaged\n- 9374 women collectors\n- 320 collection branches \n- Over 100,000 transactions\n- Equivalent of over $600,000 in bonus rewards distributed\n- Recognized for achieving 14 of 17 United Nations Sustainable Development Goals\n- Over 75 corporate partners - 10 of which have incorporated Social Plastic into their products and packaging\n\nPlastic recovery capacity: Plastic Bank is increasing momentum and is now collecting approximately 1 million kilograms of plastic per month across our global operations. 1041483 kg collected in June 2020, and 1,200,202 kg collected in July 2020. Collection numbers are verified using our proprietary blockchain platform.	2021-04-28 06:24:46.435754+00	2021-10-04 15:28:44.744822+00	\N	\N	APPROVED	https://plasticbank.com/	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/technology_036.png	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/technology_36_logo.jpg	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	f	en	f	gpml
